      <p>Whether you are creating a tutorial for YouTube, recording a product demo for your startup, or capturing a video call for reference, a reliable screen recorder is essential for every Mac user. The good news: you do not need to spend a dime. We evaluated the three best free options — <strong>OBS Studio</strong>, <strong>QuickTime Player</strong>, and <strong>CapCut</strong> — based on their feature sets, specifications, and documentation to help you find the perfect tool for your workflow.</p>

      <h2 id="how-we-evaluated">How We Evaluated</h2>
      <p>We evaluated 3 free screen recorders for Mac based on product documentation, specifications, feature analysis, and pricing comparison. Our evaluation methodology follows the <a href="/how-we-test/">ToolStep review protocol</a>, analyzing product documentation, specifications, features, and pricing. Each product was assessed across identical criteria to ensure fair comparison.</p>
      <p>We evaluated each product on four criteria: Performance (30%), Build Quality (25%), Value (20%), and Ease of Use (25%). Scores were compiled from specification analysis and feature evaluation, not marketing claims. For performance we assessed published CPU usage specifications, recording stability features, and output quality options across resolution and bitrate settings. Ease of use was evaluated based on interface design, workflow documentation, and feature accessibility for common tasks like adding a webcam overlay or trimming the final clip.</p>

      <h2 id="ranking-methodology">Ranking Methodology</h2>
      <p>Our rankings are based on weighted scoring across four dimensions:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Performance (30%)</strong> — How well does the recorder capture, encode, and deliver stable high-quality output?</li>
        <li><strong>Build Quality (25%)</strong> — Software stability, update cadence, and depth of features</li>
        <li><strong>Value (20%)</strong> — Price-to-performance ratio compared to alternatives (all three tools here are free, so value is about what you get for zero cost)</li>
        <li><strong>Ease of Use (25%)</strong> — Setup, daily use, and the learning curve from install to finished recording</li>
      </ul>

